  "doc_id": "38821",
  "text": "As mentioned above, development of cAMR is mediated by the activation of the humoral immune system; hence, the presence of HLA-DSA may be significantly associated with the development of cAMR. Indeed, the incidence of cAMR in patients with a positive crossmatch before kidney transplantation (KT) was 22% at 1-year posttransplantation. However, in ABO incompatible KT or conventional KT with low immunologic risk, the incidence was only 13% and 8%, respectively [CITATION_1] . In another report, the rate of cAMR was nearly 50% in patients with a low titer of HLA-DSA who were not desensitized before KT. On the other hand, desensitization using rituximab and plasmapheresis effectively prevented the development of cAMR [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
